{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1778291210,"nonce":"zZ0Q3unI+0sVa0sbSxjRgaFI1As=","title":"Investigate: bump activity L2 weight from 1e-5 to 1e-3 (or higher) per Michaels-2020-style regularisation","message":"## Motivation\n\nEscalation step #2 in the variance-suppression plan (efc4d68): bump `nn_hidden` and `nn_output` activity-L2 weights from 1e-5 to 1e-3.\n\n## Literature survey (2026-05-08)\n\n**C\u0026S 2019** is purely an analytical Riccati paper with no RNN training — no activity regularization values.\n\n**Shahbazi et al. 2025** (Eq. 1): hidden-unit regularization weight is `10^-5` (coefficient on `h_t^T h_t` term, plus `10^2` coefficient on `ḣ_t^T ḣ_t`). The smoothness term is much larger than the L2 term — rlrmp's efc4d68 already targets the smoothness term at 1e-3 matching this paper; the activity-L2 coefficient 1e-5 exactly matches rlrmp's current default.\n\n**Michaels et al. 2020 PNAS** (grasping RNN, parietofrontal network): exemplar network uses `nn_hidden` L2 rate regularization weight `1e-1` (reported as best overall in SI sweep: rate reg 1e-2 to 1e-1). This is 10,000× rlrmp's current value.\n\n**Sussillo et al. 2015** (Nat Neurosci): R_FR coefficient is in Supplementary Table 1, not extractable from open text. Framework reports alpha/beta/gamma hyperparameters but exact value unavailable online.\n\n## Assessment\n\nThe proposed 1e-3 value is a midpoint between rlrmp's current 1e-5 and Michaels 2020's 1e-1. It has no direct paper backing at exactly 1e-3 — it is an interpolated guess. The move is directionally motivated by Michaels 2020 (same task domain: supervised motor reaching), but the magnitude is uncertain. Testing the full range 1e-4 → 1e-2 as a mini-sweep is more principled than committing to 1e-3 specifically.\n\n## When to try\n\nAfter efc4d68 smoothness A/B result is known. If smoothness alone is insufficient for variance suppression.\n\n## Cross-refs\n\nTraining-methods coord c99ad9d. Smoothness umbrella efc4d68 (escalation step #2). Variability suppression phase f695729.","files":null}]}